    desc: "Khush Qismat Qaum (Qissa Syedna Yunus) Silsila Qasas ul Anbiya 26/30 is the twenty-sixth installment in the beloved Silsila Qasas ul Anbiya series, presenting the story of Prophet Yunus (Jonah) and the blessed nation that received his message. This volume narrates how the people of Nineveh initially rejected Prophet Yunus, how he departed in frustration and was swallowed by the great fish, and how his heartfelt Dua inside the belly of the whale became one of the most recited supplications in Islamic tradition — La ilaha illa Anta Subhanaka inni kuntu minaz-zalimin. The title 'Khush Qismat Qaum' (Fortunate Nation) refers to the extraordinary blessing that Allah bestowed upon the people of Nineveh when they ultimately repented and were spared from destruction, making them one of the rare communities in Quranic history that averted divine punishment through sincere repentance.\n\nThe book provides a detailed narrative of Prophet Yunus's mission drawn from Quranic verses in Surah As-Saffat and Surah Al-Anbiya, supported by authenticated Hadith narrations and classical Tafsir sources. It covers the Prophet's early life, his appointment as a messenger, the resistance he faced from his people, his moment of despair when he left the city without Allah's permission, the miraculous events inside the whale, and his eventual return to find that his people had genuinely turned to Allah. The author explains the lessons embedded in this story — the importance of patience in Da'wah, the danger of giving up hope in Allah's mercy, the power of sincere repentance, and the principle that no community is beyond redemption as long as they turn back to their Creator.\n\nThe storytelling approach makes this book suitable for readers of all ages, with particular appeal to young readers and families. As part of the broader thirty-volume series on the stories of the Prophets, this volume maintains the consistent quality and educational standards that have made the series popular across Urdu-reading communities. Each chapter includes discussion questions and moral reflections designed to encourage readers to apply the lessons of Prophet Yunus's story to their own lives. The book includes references to classical sources including Ibn Kathir's Qasas al-Anbiya and Al-Khazin's Tafsir, ensuring historical accuracy alongside engaging narrative.",
