    slug: "kindness-to-parents",
    desc: "KINDNESS TO PARENTS is a dedicated book that explores one of the most emphasized obligations in Islam — the duty of children to treat their parents with kindness, respect, and unwavering obedience. In the Quran, the command to be kind to parents appears immediately after the command to worship Allah alone, appearing in no fewer than six different Surahs, which indicates the immense importance Islam places on this relationship. This book systematically presents all the relevant Quranic verses, Hadith narrations, and scholarly discussions on parental rights, providing readers with a thorough understanding of what Islam expects from children toward their parents.\n\nThe book begins with a detailed analysis of the key Quranic verses on this topic, including the famous verse in Surah Al-Isra (17:23-24) where Allah commands: 'And your Lord has decreed that you worship none but Him, and that you be kind to parents. Whether one or both of them attain old age in your life, say not to them a word of contempt, nor repel them, but address them in terms of honor.' The author provides an in-depth Tafsir (explanation) of each component of this verse, explaining the significance of the pairing between worship of Allah and kindness to parents, the specific behaviors prohibited when dealing with elderly parents, and the Dua that Allah teaches children to make for their parents. The book also analyzes the verses in Surah Luqman, Surah Al-Baqarah, Surah An-Nisa, Surah Al-An'am, and Surah Al-Ahqaf that address the parent-child relationship.\n\nThe Hadith section presents dozens of narrations from the Prophet Muhammad (peace be upon him) on the rights of parents, including the Hadith stating that the pleasure of Allah lies in the pleasure of parents and the anger of Allah lies in the anger of parents, the Hadith categorizing disobedience to parents as one of the major sins, the narrations about the reward for honoring parents, and the specific accounts of how the Prophet treated his own parents (both living and deceased). The book also addresses contemporary issues that affect the parent-child relationship — including the challenge of caring for elderly parents in modern nuclear families, the Islamic perspective on placing parents in care facilities, balancing obedience to parents with other obligations, and dealing with parents who are non-Muslims or who make unreasonable demands. Written in clear English with comprehensive references, this book is an essential resource for every Muslim household.",
    meta: "KINDNESS TO PARENTS — comprehensive guide on Islamic parental rights with Quranic verses, Prophetic Hadith, and guidance on elder care and family obligations."
